EPA: Adjust WorkDay load for International
As an EPA System Admin, I need the WorkDay load into EPA to dynamically adjust a worker’s Location based on the worker’s Center, so that Centers flagged for alternate Locations load to the correct Location instead of the default.

This enhancement will allow specific Centers (e.g., C090049) instead of loading to the default Location (e.g., L5000) to load to an alternate Location (e.g., L5003) based on a configurable mapping.

The solution must be data-driven (e.g., via a DIM attribute or control structure) so that Centers can be modified to use a different Location so Location assignments can be changed or added without requiring a TI code change.

The logic will be applied during the WorkDay inbound load and will only override the default Location when a valid Center-to-Location mapping exists.
